  "text": "In this context, we have recently designed and characterized DOXloaded mixed micelles (MMDOX) composed of D-α-tocopheryl polyethylene glycol 1000 succinate (TPGS) and Tetronic® T1107. We demonstrated an enhanced in vitro antitumoral efficacy of these MMDOX versus Doxil® in breast (MDA-MB-231) and ovarian (SKOV-3) human cancer cell lines [CITATION_1] . In our case, TPGS was used as an interesting alternative to replace PEG and improve the cellular drug internalization in comparison to Doxil®, as it has been stated that TPGS https://doi.org/10.1016/j.taap.2018.07.019 Received 11 May 2018; Received in revised form 16 July 2018; Accepted 18 July 2018 may inhibit P-glycoprotein (P-gp), the efflux pump that mediates multidrug resistance in tumor cells [CITATION_2] .",
